  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PeruTM10.4">
<l>tottalarpūñ curikuḻaṟkai kēci collāl toṉṉakaran tuṟantutuṟaik kaṅkai taṉṉaip</l>
<l>pattiyuṭaik kukaṉkaṭatta vaṉampōyp pukkup parataṉukkup pātukamu maracu mīntu</l>
<l>cittirakū ṭattiruntāṉ ṟaṉṉai yiṉṟu tillainakart tiruccitra kūṭan taṉṉuḷ</l>
<l>ḷettaṉaiyuṅ kaṇkuḷirak kāṇap peṟṟa virunilattārk kimaiyavarnē rovvār tāmē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The unblinking-ones themselves shall not be equal in comparison</l>
<l>with the inhabitants of [this] vast world who got to see [Him] even a little, today,</l>
<l>so that [their] eyes are much refreshed, inside Tiruccitrakūṭam in the town of Tillai,</l>
<l rend="indent">Him who sat in Citrakūṭa,</l>
<l rend="indent">having abandoned the ancient city because of the words of Kaikeyī</l>
<l rend="indent">with curly hair [adorned with] flowers blossoming in clusters,</l>
<l rend="indent">reached and entered the forest</l>
<l rend="indent">as Guha, who bears devotion, took [Him] across the river Ganges,</l>
<l rend="indent">[and] given the sandals and the kingdom to Bharata.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
